snippet: Hours after the military-led government dedicated a memorial to the uprisings that toppled two authoritarian presidents in two years, protesters swarmed the monument.
abstract: Hours after the military-led government dedicated a memorial to the uprisings that toppled two authoritarian presidents in two years, protesters swarmed the monument.

byline.original: By ROBERT MACKEY and LIAM STACK

headline.main: Egyptian Protesters Destroy Tahrir Square Monument Erected by Interim Government
